        "FIGREF1": {
            "text": "Figure 2: (A) Lung ultrasound demonstrates area of consolidation prior to placing patient in prone position. Consolidation is non-aerated lung, which results in a significant shunt. (B) Lung ultrasound after placing patient in prone position demonstrates significant \u201cB lines\u201d (arrows) consistent with acute respiratory distress syndrome, however with improved aeration. Clinically, the patient's oxygenation improved as well after proning. (C) Linear probe demonstrates a thickened pleural line (arrows).",
            "type": "figure"
